  "title": "Clifford Beaty",
  "text": "ANGOLA — We are sad to announce that on Thursday, Jan. 30, 2025, we had to say goodbye to our beloved father, Clifford E. “Gene” Beaty.\nGene was born on Dec. 5, 1929, in Auburn, Indiana.\nHe married Audrey M. Kelly on Nov. 17, 1950. They lived many years in Auburn before moving to Angola, Indiana.\nGene worked at the Auburn Post Office and after retirement enjoyed all the activities of living at the lake.\nHis wife, Audrey, preceded him in death on March 27, 2018, and his son, Brent, on June 8, 2024.\nHe is survived by his daughters, Pamela (Sebert) and Lori Lantz; his daughter-in-law, Marymae Beaty; his grandchildren, Taylor Beaty, Kelly Harness and Mark Lantz; and his great-grandchildren.\nThere will be no services.\nPreferred memorials may be directed to Heart to Heart Hospice Care, 5646 Coventry Lane, Fort Wayne, IN 46804.\nTo send condolence, visit www.fellerandclark.com.",
